## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all perspectives on the topic. Some sources may have inherent biases, and the effectiveness of rehabilitation programs can vary based on implementation and context. Additionally, the data does not account for long-term impacts beyond the immediate reduction in recidivism rates. Further research is needed to explore the broader societal impacts of rehabilitation programs.

